    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "From the example above, we have three statements:",
      "html": "<p>From the example above, we have three statements:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The first statement is executed first (print \"Hello World!\" to the screen). Then the second statement is executed (print \"Have a good day!\" to the screen). And at last, the third statement is executed (end the C program successfully).",
      "html": "<p>The first statement is executed first (print \"Hello World!\" to the screen).<br/>\nThen the second statement is executed (print \"Have a good day!\" to the screen).<br/>\nAnd at last, the third statement is executed (end the C program successfully).</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "You will learn more about statements while reading this tutorial. For now, just remember to always end them with a semicolon to avoid any errors.",
      "html": "<p>You will learn more about statements while reading this tutorial. For now, just remember to always end them with a semicolon to avoid any errors.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Coming up: The next chapter will teach you how to control the output and how to insert new lines to make it more readable.",
